bumblebee (3.1-1~raringppa1) raring; urgency=low

  * New upstream release
    - Support for primus as an alternative to virtualgl as optirun back-end.
      Added a new Bridge option in bumblebee.conf to set the default back-end
      (auto as default currently, selects VirtualGL if installed, else primus,
      detection order may change in 4.0). optirun gained a -b/--bridge option
      for on-the-fly back-end choice.
    - Use of non-blocking sockets, replacing former 3.0.1 hotfix for socket
      polling.
    - Added an udev rule to fix nvidia card randomly turning on.
    - Fixed the three remaining compilation warnings.
    - A little fix for Kepler generation cards was added in xorg.conf.nvidia
    - A little fix for dual nvidia hybrid systems.
    - Fixed nouveau not working under X.org 1.13+.
    - Upstart dependencies changed to fix some issues.
    - Fixed available drivers detection by supporting module aliases.
  * Ubuntu changes
    - Support for all existing flavors of nvidia proprietary drivers with a new
      modprobe blacklist file and a new upstart initscript for driver detection.
  * debian/control:
    - Suggest primus.
  * debian/pachtes:
    - drop 006-set-vgl-readback-pbo.patch [upstream]
    - drop 007-nvidia-fallback-probe.patch: Replaced by the new upstart script.

 -- Bruno Pagani <bruno.n.pagani@gmail.com>  Mon, 25 Feb 2013 01:03:10 +0100

